com.qrmedia.commons.multispi.provider
Class ServiceClassnameAttributeProvider

java.lang.Object
  com.qrmedia.commons.multispi.provider.ServiceClassnameAttributeProvider
All Implemented Interfaces:
ServiceImplementationProvider
@ThreadSafe
public class ServiceClassnameAttributeProvider
extends Object

Returns those entries in a manifest that contain an attribute whose name matches the requested service class' simple name.

Does not check if the classes listed in the configuration file actually implement the requested interface!

4 Dec 2010

findServiceImplementations

public Set<String> findServiceImplementations(Class<?> serviceClass)
Description copied from interface: ServiceImplementationProvider
Returns a set of fully-qualified class names of implementations of the given service class. Is not required to check if the classes returned actually implement the requested interface or abstract class. Never returns null.

Specified by:
findServiceImplementations in interface ServiceImplementationProvider
Parameters:
serviceClass - the (non-null) requested service class
Returns:
a non-null set of fully-qualified class names of presumed implementations of the requested service
